# laken project defaults

## Scope

- Run commands from the repo root (`pyproject.toml`, `uv.lock`).
- Product-code edits belong under `src/` and `tests/`; environment guidance belongs in `AGENTS.md`, `.cursor/`, or README docs.

## Environment

- Follow `AGENTS.md` for uv, WSL, `.venv`, and command details.
- Use `uv run <tool>` for Python tools; run `uv sync` on first use and after dependency changes.
- Never delete or recreate `.venv` unless the user explicitly asks in the current message.

## Do not hand-edit or commit

- `.venv/` (no deletes, no edits inside)
- Generated outputs/caches: `dist/`, `build/`, `*.egg-info/`, `.pytest_cache/`, `.ruff_cache/`
- Local lakehouse / Spark artifact dirs from `.gitignore`

## Style and changes

- Match Ruff settings in `pyproject.toml`: line length 100, target `py311`, rules E/F/I/UP/B/SIM.
- Prefer minimal, focused diffs; no drive-by refactors.
- Do not add comments or docstrings unless the user asks.

## Tests by area

- Changes under `src/laken/deploy/` → run at least `uv run pytest tests/deploy -q`.
- Broader lakehouse changes → run the full suite with `uv run pytest`.
